Google Analytics Connection

Create a remote connection using the Google Analytics connector to sync Google Analytics data to CRM Analytics.

NOTE As of July 1, 2023, Google Analytics has been deprecated in favor of Google Analytics 4. For more information, see Google Analytics 4 has replaced Universal Analytics.

On the Data Manager Connections tab, click New Connection.
Click the name of the connector, and click Next.
Enter the connector settings.
To validate your settings and attempt to connect to the source, click Save & Test. If the connection fails, CRM Analytics shows possible reasons.

Use a Google service account instead of a user account to grant access to your Google Analytics data. For more information about Google service accounts, see Google's documentation.

Connector Settings:

* Name: Enter a name for the connector.
* Connection Type: Select "Google Analytics" from the dropdown menu.
* API Key: Enter your Google Analytics API key.
* Service Account Credentials: Upload your Google service account credentials file.

CRM Analytics creates a GLOBAL_ACCESS_OBJECT virtual object containing fields from the other virtual objects. Use this object to prepare datasets for more complex scenarios.

Eight of the virtual objects contain only dimensions. You can't connect to these objects.

The Google Core Reporting API includes these limits:

* Up to 7 dimensions and 10 measures per connection.
* Up to one million rows per virtual object. When syncing more than one million rows, CRM Analytics aggregates data from the extra rows and syncs it as a row marked "Others." To sync more than one million rows for an object, consider using the Google BigQuery connector.

To manually migrate to the improved V4 version before July 2023 when Google retires Universal Analytics:

1. Create a Google Analytics Core Reporting v4 Connection mirroring the settings of your legacy connection and any new required properties.
2. Update your recipes and dataflows to use the external objects from the new connection.
3. Keep the legacy version of the connection for troubleshooting.
